A 19-YEAR-OLD student, looking to cool off from the heat, drowned in a campus swimming pool on Friday. Mpofu Mseleku had jumped into the pool at the University of Zululand in the presence of other students.  He said other students immediately called for help. “Police divers came to the scene and searched for him under the water, but it was already too late as he was not breathing. They then certified him dead.” He said Mpofu was a student who lived at a residence on campus. University spokeswoman Gcina Nhleko said they had heard about the drowning.  “We’ll release a statement once we’ve gathered the details,” said Nhleko. KZN police spokeswoman Captain Nqobile Gwala confirmed the incident and said an inquest docket was being investigated by the Mtunzini cops. “It appears that on 18 October at 7.45pm, a 19-year-old man went to swim in a pool in KwaDlangezwa. “He jumped into the water but was unable to swim and drowned. His body was found at the bottom of the swimming pool. The circumstances surrounding the incident are being investigated,” said Gwala.